title: -webkit-
description: The `-webkit-` CSS vendor prefix is used for experimental properties and features specific to WebKit-based browsers like Chrome and Safari. It ensures compatibility and correct rendering of CSS styles in older versions of browsers.
content: The vendor prefix used in WebKit-based browsers to enable experimental CSS features and properties. The prefix supports various properties, such as `transition` or `transform`, ensuring that styles are rendered accurately in older versions of Safari and Chrome browsers.
